 Schuyler quoted the fifth paragraph of this letter in his letter to Hancock of 23 Feb. 1776 (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. National Archives and Records Administration, Papers of the Continental Congress, Washington, D.C. ]">DNA:PCC</span>, item 153).</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>The letter-book copy in <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span> reads explaining the doubt we were in respecting his detachment is r[e]cieved.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>All of the other manuscript copies read your power.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Elisha Porter commanded the Massachusetts regiment raised for service in Canada until August when he resigned because of illness.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>All of the other manuscript copies read these accounts.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>The copies in PCC read under the direction of.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>For GWs negotiations with the Caughnawaga Indians, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0161" class="document">Speeches of the Caughnawaga, St. Johns, and Passamaquoddy Indians, 31 Jan.</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0173" class="document">GW to Schuyler, 1 Feb. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0007-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0007">7</a>

   <p>See Arnold to David Wooster, 2 Jan., quoted in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0118&amp;expandNote=GEWN-03-03-02-0118-fn-0003#GEWN-03-03-02-0118-fn-0003" class="document">Schuyler to GW, 22 Jan. 1776, n.3</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0008-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0145-fn-0008">8</a>

   <p>GW is referring to the shortage of gunpowder in his army. For Henry Knoxs removal of artillery from Ticonderoga, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0019" class="document">Knox to GW, 5 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
